<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12016h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12016h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12016h"> 16(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> model / On me vende partout</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Schur&eacute; meets a strange-looking figure, a simpleton, he thinks, &lsquo;un innocent&rsquo;): Voyant qu&apos;il m&apos;int&eacute;ressait, il mit le point sur la hanche, comme pour me faire admirer sa pose. &ldquo;Qui &ecirc;tes-vous? lui dis-je. &mdash; Marchand de coquilles et mod&egrave;le d&apos;atelier. Tous les peintres qui viennent ici font mon portrait. Voulez-vous [136]</font> que je pose pour vous? &mdash; Je ne suis pas peintre, malheureusement. &mdash; Voulez-vous faire le tour du Mont sur les gr&egrave;ves? je vous conduirai. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Chemin faisant, l&apos;innocent m&apos;&eacute;num&eacute;rait tous les tableaux pour lesquels il avait pos&eacute;, et il ajoutait avec un tranquille orgueil, en &eacute;tendant ses bras et en se baignant ses haillons dans le soleil couchant: &ldquo;<mark>On me vend dans le monde entier.</mark>&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[Seeing that I was interested, he put the point on his hip, as if he wanted me to admire his pose. &ldquo;Who are you?&rdquo; said I? &mdash; Seller of shells and painter&apos;s model. All the painters who come here have made my portrait. Do you want me to pose for you? But I am not a painter, unfortunately. Do you want to walk around the Mont on the strand? I&apos;ll guide you. [&hellip;]</font> On the way the innocent one mentioned all the paintings that he had posed for and with a quiet pride he added, while extending his arms and enjoying the last rays of a setting sun: &ldquo;I am sold all over the world.&rdquo;] <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 136-7</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Fr. I am sold everywhere. </mm> </dd></dl>
